  "requiresDevice": [],
  "designNotes": "Clear the wardens, then route the beam across the middle chamber (emitter fires +x at z=-1): one player rotates the emitter mount to state 1 to retract the aperture rib, freeze the steam column to drop the second beam-blocking rib, and socket the fetched prism where the beam crosses x=0 — the prism relays the beam -z down the corridor; the other player holds the receiver-side shutter plate to open the beam shutter so the relayed beam reaches r1, lighting it and opening the exit door.",
  "intro": "One prism, two gates of light. Freeze the column to bend the beam \u2014 and hold the shutter while the mount comes round.",
